accessibility.text: Ceteris Paribus
If only price changes and Incomes, Tastes, Expectations and Prices of other goods remain the same
How will buyers react to a decrease in the price of cars?
Quantity Demanded increases
What if at the same time that car prices drop, incomes also drop?
Two variables changed (income and prices) we can not know if consumers would buy more because of the price drop or fewer because of the drop in income…
